# Feature Card style

Use **Feature Cards** for compact, accent-tinted highlight tiles (not full `SurfaceCard` white blocks).

**Used on:** Home Insights rail, Expenses chart insight, Budget featured cards (Monthly Income / Monthly Budget).

## Shared primitives

Import from `src/app/components/ui/featureCard.ts` and `FeatureCardIcon.tsx`:

- `FEATURE_CARD` — shadow, radius, padding, icon size, eyebrow/headline/detail typography
- `featureCardGradient(accentBg)` — `linear-gradient(145deg, accentBg 0%, #FFFFFF 55%)`
- `featureCardSurface(accentBg, options?)` — gradient + shadow + radius + padding
- `<FeatureCardIcon accentColor accentBg categoryId? iconKey? phosphorIcon? />`

## Required visuals

| Element | Rule |
|--------|------|
| **Background** | `featureCardGradient(accentBg)` — never flat `#FFFFFF` for the card body |
| **Shadow** | `FEATURE_CARD.shadow` (`0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.07)`) |
| **Icon** | Always `FeatureCardIcon` at **sm** (36×36, radius 10): Phosphor **light** on `accentBg`, or `CategoryIcon` / `CategoryIconPreview` |
| **Accent pair** | Each card gets distinct `accentColor` + `accentBg` (category colors or semantic palette) |

## Typography (when using insight-style copy)

- **Eyebrow:** `FEATURE_CARD.eyebrow` — 9px uppercase gray
- **Headline:** `FEATURE_CARD.headline` — 16px, weight 800, `#1A1A2E`, letter-spacing -0.5
- **Detail:** `FEATURE_CARD.detail` — 11px `#6B7280`

Content layout may vary (progress bars, amounts, grid vs full-width); **gradient + icon rules are fixed**.

## Layout patterns

- **Compact insight (2-col grid, expense insight):** row — text left, `FeatureCardIcon` right; `FEATURE_CARD.padding`, `FEATURE_CARD.radius`
- **Featured budget (full width):** row header with icon + title + edit affordance; custom body (amount, progress bar); `FEATURE_CARD.radiusLg`, `FEATURE_CARD.paddingLg`

## Icons

- Categories → `categoryId` on `FeatureCardIcon`
- Configured glyphs → `iconKey` from `CategoryIconKey` (e.g. `wallet`, `piggy`)
- Insight phosphors → `phosphorIcon`: `trend-up`, `arrows-clockwise`, `chart-line-up`, `target`

Do **not** use filled Phosphor icons or ad-hoc 44px icon boxes on Feature Cards.

## Do not

- Mix flat white card backgrounds with Feature Card icons
- Duplicate gradient/icon constants — use `featureCard.ts` / `FeatureCardIcon`
- Use emoji or non-Phosphor icon libraries (see `phosphor-icons-only` rule)
